<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Healthful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Healthful,</orth> 1) free from disease, sound: <bibl n="shak. son 118.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 118, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.319" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 319</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 38</bibl>.<lb />2) wholesome, salutary: <cit><quote>a bath and h. remedy for men diseased,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 154.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 154, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>makes us early stirrers, which is both h. and good husbandry,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>gave h. welcome to their shipwrecked guests,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 115</bibl></cit> (F<hi rend="sub">2. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 115</bibl> 4</hi> <emph>helpful</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>